Saker

The browser video editor in web-editor-next/ contains code derived from
OpenCut (https://github.com/OpenCut-app/OpenCut), licensed under the MIT
License. Saker-specific changes are also licensed under the project license.

The editor ships flag SVG assets under web-editor-next/public/flags/. These
assets use the flag-icons naming/source convention and are treated as
third-party MIT-licensed assets; see web-editor-next/ASSET_LICENSES.md.

The embedded model pricing and context window data in
pkg/model/data/model_prices_and_context_window.json is sourced from the
BerriAI/litellm project (https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm), licensed under
the MIT License.

The hooks system, event types, settings format, and CLAUDE.md loader are
implemented following the Claude Code (Anthropic) publicly documented
specification. See https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code for the
reference specification.

Dependency license inventory is maintained in docs/third-party-notices.md.
